<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{1},{3}\right)}</m></li><li><image width="52%" pi:generated="problems/images/mom-809298-2.png"/>
</li></ul></p><p>The form of a parabola is <m>\displaystyle{y}={a}{\left({x}-{h}\right)}^{{2}}+{k}</m>. Because this parabola is <m>\displaystyle{y}={2}{\left({x}+{1}\right)}^{{2}}+{3}</m>, which can be written <m>\displaystyle{y}={2}{\left({x}-{\left(-{1}\right)}\right)}^{{2}}+{\left({3}\right)}</m> we know the following.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{h}=-{1}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{k}={3}</m>. Thus the vertex is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{1},{3}\right)}</m>.</p>
<p>To graph the parabola we can use the vertex and another convenient point. One convenient point is at <m>\displaystyle{x}=-{1}+{1}={0}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={2}{\left({0}-{\left(-{1}\right)}\right)}^{{2}}+{\left({3}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle={2}{\left({1}\right)}^{{2}}+{\left({3}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle={2}+{\left({3}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle={5}</m>.</p>
<p>We use <m>\displaystyle{\left({0},{5}\right)}</m>.</p>
</solution>
